description: Kallikrein-related peptidase 7 (KLK7) is a serine peptidase that is over-produced in the most lethal form of ovarian cancer, called high grade serous ovarian cancer (HGSOC). To determine its underlying molecular mechanism of action, a comprehensive analysis of KLK7 degradome in the OVMZ-6 cell-secreted proteins was performed using two complementary proteomic approaches, quantitative PROtein Topography and Migration Analysis Platform (qPROTOMAP) and Terminal Amine Isotopic Labelling of Substrates (TAILS).
